/*******************************************************************************
 * CHIP:  BCMI_PEREGRINE5_PC_XGXS
 * REGISTER:  TLB_RX_PRBS_CHK_EN_TMR_CTL
 * BLOCKS:   TLB_RX
 * REGADDR:  0x6004
 * DEVAD:    1
 * DESC:     TLB RX PRBS Checker Enable Timer Control
 * RESETVAL: 0x0 (0)
 * ACCESS:   R/W
 * FIELDS:
 *     PRBS_CHK_EN_TIMER_UNIT_SEL prbs_chk_en timer unit select.3'd0 => prbs_chk_en timer is disabled and PRBS checker mode is enabled as per prbs_chk_en register.3'd1 => use use heartbeat_toggle_1us   as timer unit. when linktrn_rx_prbs_chk_en = 1 then it is 1    linktrn frame heartbeat3'd2 => use use heartbeat_toggle_10us  as timer unit. when linktrn_rx_prbs_chk_en = 1 then it is 10   linktrn frame heartbeat3'd3 => use use heartbeat_toggle_100us as timer unit. when linktrn_rx_prbs_chk_en = 1 then it is 100  linktrn frame heartbeat3'd4 => use use heartbeat_toggle_1ms   as timer unit. when linktrn_rx_prbs_chk_en = 1 then it is 1000 linktrn frame heartbeat3'd5 => use use heartbeat_toggle_10ms  as timer unit. when linktrn_rx_prbs_chk_en = 1 then it is 1    linktrn frame heartbeat3'd6 => use use heartbeat_toggle_100ms as timer unit. when linktrn_rx_prbs_chk_en = 1 then it is 1    linktrn frame heartbeatOther values: ReservedMake sure that only one of the 2 register settings ((prbs_chk_en_timer_unit_sel >=1 & prbs_chk_en_timer_unit_timeout > 0) and prbs_chk_burst_err_cnt_en) are TRUE at any given time and not simultaneously TRUE.
 *     PRBS_CHK_NEW_TIMER_MODE PRBS checker new timer mode enable.1 - keep the prbs checker always active irrespective of timer is enabled or not. Error counters will only count while timer is still active.timer can be started by writing prbs_chk_en_timer_unit_sel to 0 followed by a >=1 timer_unit_sel value. timer can also be started by reading the error counter prbs_chk_err_cnt_msb if prbs_chk_en_timer_unit_sel is already >=1 .0 - if timer mode is enabled then prbs checker and error counting will be only enabled while timer is active (backward compatible default mode).
 *     PRBS_CHK_EN_TIMER_UNIT_TIMEOUT PRBS checker timer timeout value.Should be programmed before enabling the PRBS checker in timer mode. Timer value = prbs_chk_en_timer_unit_timeout * timer_unit selected by prbs_chk_en_timer_unit_sel.Valid range: 1 to 1022
 *
 ******************************************************************************/
